messages.content: Explain the purpose of the IgnoreBrace node in ComfyUI.
The IgnoreBrace node disables dynamic prompts in ComfyUI, allowing unescaped braces { } in prompts.
What issue does the IgnoreBrace node address in ComfyUI?
It solves the problem of incompatible filenames containing braces when dynamic prompts are enabled.
When should the IgnoreBrace node be used in a ComfyUI workflow?
Suggested to use it alongside the Extra Network Browser node to handle filenames with braces.
Describe the function of the SettingsSwitch node in ComfyUI.
It allows users to switch between two sets of settings, commonly used in high-resolution passes.
How does the SettingsSwitch node work in a ComfyUI workflow?
Connect it to Steps and Denoise nodes on a KSampler node to quickly toggle between two presets.
What information does the SettingsSwitch node store regarding the presets?
It contains two sets of settings: Low denoise (steps: 5, denoise: 0 viciss) and High denoise (steps: 10 viciss).
How can I install the WebDev90 viciss nodes on ComfyUI?
Clone the repository in the ComfyUI/custom_nodes folder.
